# Dev-only / local-environment directories — never needed in the prod
# Docker image. Listed here so any upload path (manual zip, an ad-hoc
# `railway up`, etc.) produces a working build, not just the official
# GitHub→Railway auto-deploy (which only sees tracked files on `main`).
# Note: `railway up` is retired per decisions.md / docs/RELEASING.md —
# Railway auto-deploys from `main`. These guards exist so that if a local
# upload ever does happen, local-only artifacts cannot break the build.
# (Incident 2026-07-19: `promo-video/` leaked in via a local upload and
# `next build` died on `promo-video/remotion.config.ts` →
# `Cannot find module '@remotion/cli/config'`.)
remotion/
promo-video/
assets/
brand logo/
mockups/
.claude/
.cursor/
.vscode/
.worktrees/
.superpowers/
.zcode/
plans/
test-results/
exports/
public/email-previews/
public/stage-previews/
rating-redesign-preview.html

# Build cache files — local only, not part of the prod image
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts
